{"id":"318527813_Going_Higher_in_First-Order_Quantifier_Alternation_Hierarchies_on_Words","abstract":"We investigate quantifier alternation hierarchies in first-order logic on finite words. Levels in these hierarchies are defined by counting the number of quantifier alternations in formulas. We prove that one can decide membership of a regular language in the levels $\\mathcal{B}{\\Sigma}_2$ (finite boolean combinations of formulas having only one alternation) and ${\\Sigma}_3$ (formulas having only two alternations and beginning with an existential block). Our proofs work by considering a deeper problem, called separation, which, once solved for lower levels, allows us to solve membership for higher levels.","authors":["Thomas Place","Marc Zeitoun"],"meta":["July 2017Journal of the ACM 66(2)","DOI:10.1145/3303991"],"references":["264953401_Alternative_Automata_Characterization_of_Piecewise_Testable_Languages","263798372_Undecidability_Automata_and_Pseudovarities_of_Finite_Semigroups","242947639_Power_monoids_and_finiteJ-trivial_monoids","242604307_Monoids_of_upper-triangular_matrices","235772028_Efficient_Separability_of_Regular_Languages_by_Subsequences_and_Suffixes","226504747_A_Delay_Theorem_for_Pointlikes","226209131_An_Algorithm_to_Verify_Local_Threshold_Testability_of_Deterministic_Finite_Automata","339295232_The_tale_of_the_quantifier_alternation_hierarchy_of_first-order_logic_over_words","321518398_Elements_of_Finite_Model_Theory","320394505_The_dot-depth_hierarchy_45_years_later","318360141_Separating_regular_languages_with_two_quantifier_alternations","300051215_Separating_Regular_Languages_with_Two_Quantifiers_Alternations","285327781_Une_theorie_algebrique_du_codage","283926055_Diamonds_are_forever_The_variety_DA","282303975_Separation_and_the_successor_relation","281885951_Separating_Regular_Languages_by_Locally_Testable_and_Locally_Threshold_Testable_Languages","269024720_An_Explicit_Formula_for_the_Intersection_of_Two_Polynomials_of_Regular_Languages